The schema is clear enough to build this from `ontime.ontime` plus airport enrichment by `OriginAirportID` and `DestAirportID`. I’m probing the data shape now so the final SQL orders legs correctly, builds the full route text, and captures the most recent maximum-hop itinerary without emitting any artifact noise.
tool altinity_ontime_demo.execute_query({"query":"WITH legs AS (SELECT Tail_Number, Flight_Number_Reporting_Airline, IATA_CODE_Reporting_Airline, FlightDate, OriginAirportID, DestAirportID, Origin, Dest, toDateTime(concat(toString(FlightDate), ' ', leftPad(toString(intDiv(DepTime, 100)), 2, '0'), ':', leftPad(toString(DepTime % 100), 2, '0'), ':00')) AS dep_ts, DepTime FROM ontime.ontime WHERE Cancelled = 0 AND Diverted = 0 AND DepTime IS NOT NULL AND Tail_Number != '' AND Flight_Number_Reporting_Airline != '') SELECT Tail_Number, Flight_Number_Reporting_Airline, IATA_CODE_Reporting_Airline, FlightDate, count() AS hops, min(dep_ts) AS first_dep_ts, groupArray((dep_ts, Origin, Dest, DepTime)) AS sample_legs FROM legs GROUP BY Tail_Number, Flight_Number_Reporting_Airline, IATA_CODE_Reporting_Airline, FlightDate ORDER BY hops DESC, FlightDate DESC LIMIT 5","limit":10})
